txt.en:
'Ho la, Silent One! You saw them when you came back, didn't you? The webs, I mean.

'Damned spiders clogging up the road to Cirith Ungol every single day since Lugbúrz fell, and I can't bear to cut any more webs. I've already blunted three of my blades on 'em!

'Why don't you do me a favour and clear some of them out?'
Clear webs from the road leading to Cirith Ungol ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
New webs have been spun each day since Sauron's fall, and Práguk has tired of clearing them from the road leading to Cirith Ungol.
Cleared webs from the road leading to Cirith Ungol ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
You have cleared the road to Cirith Ungol of webs, but it is likely that spiders shall soon return to spin new webs and further irritate Práguk.
Webs can be found along the road to Cirith Ungol in western Lhingris.\n\nPráguk has asked you to clear webs from the road leading to Cirith Ungol.
You have cleared the road to Cirith Ungol of webs.
